"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-06-Colombia-s-Mariana-Paton-on-her-Paris-Olympics-loss-1vPuhszlom4-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  BMX Racing has established itself as one of the most exciting events at the Olympics. Colombia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Mariana Pajon is known as the Queen of BMX and has won gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s event at London 2012 and Rio 2016, as well as a silver medal in Tokyo three years ago. In Paris, she just missed out on a place in the final. She told CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams that she will carry on racing and says she is proud at how the sport has developed.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"